President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Jennifer Homendy as Chair of the National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB). Homendy has been a member of the NTSB since August 2018 and has over 25 years of experience in transportation safety. Prior to her appointment, she served as the Democratic Staff Director for the Subcommittee on Railroads, Pipelines, and Hazardous Materials of the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure in the U.S. House of Representatives. Homendy has also held positions with the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, Transportation Trades Department, AFL-CIO, and American Iron and Steel Institute. She holds a B.A. from The Pennsylvania State University and is currently pursuing a Master of Transportation Safety Administration from Clemson University. Homendy resides in Fredericksburg, Virginia, with her husband and daughter.